                                    jcr:title="Breaking barriers with cutting-edge research"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-01-07T17:21:36.422-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>In the field of neuroscience, there are many tough-to-treat disorders with high unmet need. Our researchers and scientists are relentless in their pursuit of raising the standards of care through innovative approaches to help patients. &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>But the brain is complex, and new challenges require new ways of thinking across all stages of drug discovery and development. That’s why we are continuously exploring innovative approaches to address some of the most prevalent and serious brain disorders, from Parkinson’s and Alzheimer’s to migraine and schizophrenia.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
